  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Project requirements documented in internal specification TR-CPB-2024-001 confirm the acceptance criterion RH < 1 and the comparative predicate-device methodology; those requirements are referenced throughout this narrative but are captured in the structured evidence record via bindsModel and bindsDataset only under the Minimal profile binding rules.",
